Start by drawing Heads Hands and Feet. A lot of artists fall short on this, and learning to do it well takes time.
Otherwise you draw great bodies, because the body is larger and easier to capture.
You'll find yourself in a pit of trying to make drawing that hide the hands and feet because you can't draw them for shit, and the heads will be smaller than the bodies every time.

Short version:
Start learning good habits for scale and perspective.
